description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Due to the huge success of the Intermediate Care Services within Frimley Health NHS Foundation Trust, we are now in the position to grow our team and advertise for an additional full time band 6 Community Occupational Therapist to work in Enhanced Recovery and Support at Home (ERS). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a new post due to ongoing investment in ERS to support closer working with the Community Nursing Teams ensuring more timely access to appropriate complex equipment for acutely unwell patients. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;With a strong interest in crisis intervention, equipment, prevention and system working you will be part of the Enhanced Recovery &amp; Support at Home team based at Fleet Hospital. Working with patients predominantly in their own homes you will not only enable them to remain at home when acutely unwell but also to return home from hospital sooner. Working in this fast paced team you will be directly managed by an OT Team Lead and be provided ongoing CPD opportunities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As well as a diverse clinical role, this post will enable you to use your broader OT skills to undertake triage and management, including direct management of junior staff and students. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The service operates 8am-8pm 7 days a week and you will be expected to work on a rota basis to cover these hours. You must be able to travel independently &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;please call Jade Cope or Jen White on 01252 813847&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
